09/11/2006
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- An Istanbul court handed down a life sentence Wednesday (November 8th) to Ercan Kartal, leader of the outlawed extreme leftist Revolutionary People's Liberation Party-Front (DHKP-C). 
He was convicted of a 1996 attack on a company's headquarters, in which several people were killed, as well an assassination plot against former President Kenan Evren. 
(Hurriyet, Focus - 09/11/06; TurkishPress.com - 08/11/06)
